The LGBTQI+ community has been subjected to hate violence in recent years, and gun violence specifically affects this community. This is evident in incidents such as the Orlando nightclub shooting, violence against transgender women, and the recent attack in Colorado Springs. Places that should be safe for the LGBTQI+ community are often turned into sites of terror and violence. The article emphasizes the need to address the inequalities that contribute to violence against LGBTQI+ people and calls for action to combat gun violence. The author expresses condolences for the victims and their families and urges for an assault weapons ban to remove weapons of war from American streets.